what type of miniature horse stallion mare gelding etc should a beginner get i am new to minis and would like feedback on whether i should get a stallion mare gelding colt or filly as my first mini what are the pros and cons of them thank you for a first horse mini or regular size i would recommend a gelding they tend to be more even tempered and tolerant mares can be very moody and stallions can be very pushy unless you plan to breed then a gelding is definitely your best bet if you think breeding may be a potential future option at least start with a gelding to see what types of special care they need then start building your stable up a bit Horse Arabian horse Charisma (horse) Japan Cup Thoroughbred Welsh Cob (Section D) Przewalski's Horse Breeders' Cup Trakehner Harry Payne Whitney Selective breeding Hinny Prix de l'Arc de Triomphe Akhal-Teke Thoroughbred horse race Lipizzan Horse racing Kentucky Derby Sunday Silence Roan (color) Preakness Stakes Morgan horse Exmoor pony Karabakh Connemara pony Donkey Welsh pony of cob type (Section C) United Kingdom horse-racing Smarty Jones Oldenburg (horse) Traveller (horse) Melbourne Cup Ruffian (horse) Radio controlled airplane Sleipnir Clydesdale (breed) Dog Pony of the Americas Seabiscuit James R. Keene Hanoverian (horse) Canadian Football League Drill bit Sunline Belmont Stakes International Phonetic Alphabet Selle Fran__ais Gray (horse) Hackney (horse) Horses of Middle-earth Travers Stakes Equine conformation Tennessee Walker Holstein (horse) Montreal Alouettes Might and Power Domestication of the horse Makybe Diva New York Giants Welsh pony (Section B) Keeneland Spirit: Stallion of the Cimarron Kentucky Horse Park Chocobo Belair Stud Resistor Mule Dole Gudbrandsdal Magnetic levitation train Man O' War (horse) German grammar Pit bull Barb (horse) The Red Pony Tenterfield Terrier Spirit rover timeline for 2004 March Sindbad the Sailor Castration Zoophilia Kamboja Horsemen Miniature golf BMW Breastfeeding Jacksonville Jag